  "body": "Hi Guys,\r\n\r\nI assume geth --light mode downloads all the headers of blocks which have the roots (transaction, storage, receipt) needed for SPV clients to do verifications. I tried using web3 to grab blocks from geth and it tries to connect to peers to download blocks, is it possible to return the header in place of a block or have a getBlockHeader command which is not dependent on peers? (once you download a header it should be available).\r\n",
