    "body": "@rjl493456442 I've scanned the repo, you do have the EthereumClient which exposes https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/6fc84946203929143c51010e0a10d9fa61fb9b92/mobile/ethclient.go#L64 the header function but no RPC or clique handler.\r\n\r\nI'm running a light client alongside my protocol, a trustless bridge between two chains. Here is the data I need I can show you via unit test:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/syscoin/syscoin/blob/dev-4.x/src/test/syscoin_asset_tests.cpp#L408\r\n\r\nYou can see I use the tx root and receipt root of the header:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/syscoin/syscoin/blob/dev-4.x/src/services/assetconsensus.cpp#L71\r\n\r\nI need the receipt to check the status field, and the tx to get from, to and abi data of the burn function call from eth contract.\r\n\r\nI push roots from local client thru rpc to my protocol and use it in my conensus check above. \r\n\r\nThus I thought it'd be nice to be able to tap into getting the header since light clients already have it.\r\n\r\nHopefully that makes sense.",
